        <div id="intro">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12 section-title">INTRO</div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <img src="http://www.aceshowbiz.com/images/wennpic/paul-walker-sao-paulo-fashion-week-2013-02.jpg" class="img-responsive thumbnail" alt="paul-walker" />
                        <figcaption class="caption">Paul Walker</figcaption>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                        <p><strong>Paul William Walker IV</strong> (September 12, 1973 &#45; November 30, 2013) was an American actor. Walker began his career guest-starring in several television shows such as <strong>The Young and the Restless</strong> and <strong>Touched by an Angel</strong>. Walker gained prominence with breakout roles in <strong>Varsity Blues</strong> (1999) and <strong>She's All That</strong> (1999).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CAREER SECTION -->
        <div id="career">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12 section-title">CAREER</div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <p>Walker gained international fame for his portrayal of <strong>Brian O'Conner</strong> in <strong>The Fast and the Furious</strong> street racing franchise. His other films include <strong>Eight Below</strong>, <strong>Into the Blue</strong>, <strong>Joy Ride</strong>, and <strong>Takers</strong>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <p>Walker died on November 30, 2013, at the age of 40 as a passenger in a single-car crash alongside friend and driver <strong>Roger Rodas</strong>. Walker's father and daughter filed separate wrongful death lawsuits against Porsche, which resulted in settlements.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- PERSONAL LIFE SECTION -->
        <div id="personal-life">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12 section-title">PERSONAL LIFE</div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <p>Walker was known for his philanthropic efforts, including founding the disaster relief organization Reach Out Worldwide (ROWW) following the 2010 Haiti earthquake.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <p>He was often praised for his off-screen charitable work, and as a performer. Walker was also active in shark conservation efforts. He participated in the Billfish Foundation's annual fundraiser.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FACTS SECTION -->
        <div id="facts">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12 section-title">FACTS</div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Walker was raised as a member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.</li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> He had English and German ancestry.</li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> He enjoyed surfing at the beach near his Santa Barbara home.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> He attended Village Christian School in Sun Valley, California.</li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Walker was a keen traveler, and enjoyed exploring different cultures.</li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-check"></i> His favorite car was the Nissan Skyline GT-R R34.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
